title: Australia’s Millman downed at Shenzen Open
text:
Australia’s Millman downed at Shenzen Open Posted by AAP + on 02/10/2015 at 3:58 pm   Australia’s Millman downed at Shenzen Open 
Australia’s John Millman has missed out on a spot in the Shenzen Open quarter-finals after being beaten by second seed Marin Cilic. 
The Croatian took just shy of two hours to complete a 6-3 4-6 6-3 win and set up a quarter-final against Hyeon Chung. 
The Korean breezed through his own second-round encounter, beating Britain’s No.2 Aljaz Bedene, the seventh seed, 6-2 6-0 inside an hour. 
Spanish fourth seed Guillermo Garcia-Lopez beat Czech Lukas Rosol 6-4 6-3, while Adrian Mannarino, the fifth seed from France, saw off China’s Yan Bai 7-5 7-6 (9-7).
